This paper discusses the use of GPUs for database management systems, which falls under the category of computer science databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions challenges related to data processing and memory bandwidth, which are relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and computer architecture (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper discusses optimization techniques, which are relevant to compiler optimization (cs.CC) and programming languages (cs.PL).
